    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="611"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Sir <persName
                            type="to">Julian Pauncefote</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 14, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 220.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to previous correspondence
                    concerning the seizure of the <hi rend="italic">Shelby</hi> and certain other
                    British sealing vessels, I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of your
                    note of the 10th instant, stating that you have received a telegram from
                    Rear-Admiral Stephenson asking that measures may be taken to secure the
                    immediate attendance of the commander and officers of the U. S. S. <hi
                        rend="italic">Corwin</hi> and, in due time, of other officers who can give
                    evidence regarding the seizure of the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi> and the
                        <hi rend="italic">E. B. Marvin.</hi>
                </p>
                <p>In reply I beg to inform you that measures had already been taken to secure the
                    immediate presence of the officers of the <hi rend="italic">Corwin</hi> at
                    Victoria as witnesses in the case of the <hi rend="italic">Shelby</hi>, and that
                    I have hastened to bring the contents of your note to the attention of the
                    Secretary of the Treasury in order that suitable action may be promptly taken in
                    regard to the other cases.</p>
                <p>I shall be obliged for early information as to the time when the libels against
                    the British sealing vessels <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi> and <hi
                        rend="italic">E. B. Marvin</hi> will be brought to trial.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
